news.title: Eviction notices issued to 41 houses in Hapur
news.para: In the legal notice, the Hapur Municipal Corporation alleged that 41 homes were constructed on 10 bighas of land belonging to the civic authority.

news.title: GOA: ACB investigation of SEZ land allotment still incomplete after 13 years
news.para: ​​The complaint states that the allotment was done by hatching a criminal conspiracy, and involved manipulation of documents, cheating govt and causing loss to the exchequer.

news.title: DLF to open three shopping malls in Goa, Delhi and Gurugram in FY26
news.para: At present, DLF Group has 8 retail properties, including a large shopping mall in Noida, with a portfolio of around 45 lakh square feet space.

news.title: Growth momentum in residential sector will continue in coming months: CBRE
news.para: The demand was driven by several positive factors, including a growing desire for homeownership, rising income levels, and continuous infrastructure development.

news.title: Nearly 20 shopping malls to be operational by 2026-end in top eight cities: Report
news.para: The consultant noted that as many as 19 Grade A shopping malls covering 12.3 million (123 lakh) square feet of new retail space will become operational in 2025 and 2026 calendar years.

news.title: Coimbatore civic body's commercial complexes fail to general expected revenue
news.para: Other corporation-owned shops and complexes in areas such as DB Road, Patel Road, and Ram Nagar face similar challenges, with many remaining shuttered.

news.title: New Town residents in Kolkata can now pay property tax on NKDA's website
news.para: The authorities received feedback from citizens about hurdles in paying property tax and fees for other municipal services through the e-district portal.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body proposes significant reduction in property tax rates for parking areas
news.para: Since 2008, property owners in the city have paid property tax on areas earmarked for parking. The applicable rate was historically pegged at 50% of the UAV of the main property.

news.title: Ghaziabad: GDA to allot slots to buyers for registration of their properties
news.para: On an average, the Authority processes over 80 registries a month, which is at least 11 a day. The bulk of its revenue also comes from the sale of plots and flats.

news.title: KL Rahul and Suniel Shetty acquire land parcel in Thane for ₹9.85 crore
news.para: The transaction incurred a stamp duty of ₹68.96 lakh and registration charges of ₹30,000, according to the Inspector General of Registration (IGR) documents reviewed by Square Yards. The transaction was registered in March 2025.

news.title: KHB to develop new layouts spread over 2,500 acres in Mysuru
news.para: KHB, which successfully developed layouts in Yelwal, Hootagally, and Kenchalagudu in Mysuru, has now initiated this project in view of the demand for its sites and housing quarters in the district.

news.title: Vijayawada civic body nets Rs 252 crore property tax revenue in FY25
news.para: Officials attribute the increase in tax collection to the five percent discount provided to households for paying the entire property and VLT taxes in a single transaction, which evoked a good response from taxpayers in the city.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body achieves 95% property tax target in FY25
news.para: While the shortfall was just Rs 280 crore, there were significant variations in zonal achievements with some exceeding expectations and others lagging behind.

news.title: Mysuru: Muda housing project shelved despite positive response from people
news.para: For the last four years, in its annual budget presentation, Muda had announced allocating of Rs 250 crore for the proposed project. However, this year, in the 2025-26 budget presentation, there is no mention of the project.

news.title: Haryana RERA urges DTCP to take final call on three housing projects by OSB
news.para: Rera has now recommended two options to the department: either restore the licences and allow OSB to complete the projects, or assign the task to another competent agency to ensure timely possession of homes to allottees.

news.title: NCLAT dismisses Supertech promoter's plea against personal insolvency proceedings
news.para: Arora's counsel submitted the insolvency proceedings initiated against Supertech Ltd under Section 7 is currently sub-judice before the Supreme Court.

news.title: Shaan and his wife acquire property in Pune for ₹10 crore
news.para: The plot spans approximately 0.4 hectares (4,787.92 sq yard), while the built-up area of the bungalow is around 5,500 sq ft. (511.04 sq meters).

news.title: Noida residents raise civic infrastructure issues with Uttar Pradesh minister
news.para: Residents pointed out that despite Noida's rapid population growth, the expansion of civic amenities has not kept pace.

news.title: Arnya Realestates Fund Advisors invests ₹130 crore in Casagrand's project in Bengaluru
news.para: The firm had announced its first investment in October 2024 for a project in Navi Mumbai and this is their second investment.

news.title: Arpora-Nagoa gram sabha to request Goa CM for regularization of illegal structures
news.para: ​Following appeals from villagers, sarpanch Roshan Redkar said that the panchayat will write to the chief minister and other authorities, requesting them to regularise all affected structures.
